<div id="banner">
	<h1>CBDTPA Requires Open Source</h1>
</div>

<div class="content">
<p>I was reading through <a href="http://www.politechbot.com/docs/cbdtpa/hollings.s2048.032102.html">the text of the CBDTPA (Consumer Broadband and Digital Television Promotion Act)</a> and noticed that it specifically requires that &#8220;any software portion of such [DRM] standards is based on open source code&#8221;. Odd&#8230;</p>

